BT /F1 10.5 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 301 Tm (The trailer should sell contrast:) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 280 Tm (1. A castle room, still and luxurious.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 266 Tm (2. Dracula crosses a blood-red threshold at night.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 252 Tm (3. A villager window goes dark.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 238 Tm (4. An earth crate is dragged through mist.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 224 Tm (5. A church bell begins ringing at dawn.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 210 Tm (6. Daylight map state: roads marked, fires lit, one refuge burned.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 196 Tm (7. Night again: Dracula chooses another route.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 182 Tm (8. The port and the Demeter appear as the objective.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.5 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 168 Tm (9. Final line: "Prepare the passage before the land wakes.") Tj ET
